Description:
Executive Residence in a Family Locale
Set in the heart of Drysdale, this impressive executive residence features a suite of amenities associated with the most discerning of lifestyles. The brand new three-bedroom modern residence boasts an endless list of quality fixtures and fittings and a striking and contemporary interior. An open-plan main living area and modern kitchen, which has plenty of natural sunlight, opens to a perfect and serene outdoor entertainment area. It is undercover, making it easy to host large family functions right in your own backyard. The large master bedroom comprises WIR and large en suite, whilst the further 2 spacious bedrooms have access to the central bathroom with large bath and shower. Other benefits of this stunning abode include an executive study, theatre room with projector, 2KW Solar System, ducted heating/cooling system and DLUG plus a second DLUG/workshop for the car enthusiasts. Ideally located in a quiet family precinct.

Description:
Lifestyle Property on 1 Acre in heart of town
Immaculately presented Family home on 1 acre, this property has been continually developed over the past 18 years by the current owner. Fully landscaped to offer a low maintenance private rural outlook with pockets of green lawns and open spaces. The home comprises 4 bedrooms 2 bathrooms 2 livings rooms and plenty of storage cupboards. Features include double remote garage, gas ducted heating, great covered entertainment BBQ area. fully paved walkways, brick lined driveway to the rear of the property, large Zincalume shed suit car store age and workshop, fully fenced chook pen and run adjoining vege garden and a replica of "Craigs Hut" complete with sheltered camp fire and rustic seating. All of this set in a great location close to centre of town, schools and the rail trail. inspection recommended

Description:
RURAL LIVING IN PERIOD HOME, (APP. 4 ACRES)
Refurbished with style and flair, whilst maintaining the warmth of a period home...just beautiful! Open plan living includes fantastic kitchen with walk-in pantry, meals and living with adjacent formal dining or extra living space allowing flexibility. Three spacious bedrooms (one extra large) two with BIR'S, ensuite plus central bathroom which functions 2-way and a separate laundry. Doors open from the living room to huge undercover patio which provides extra room for informal living. Features include polished floors, claw footed bath, high ceilings, fretwork, cornices, ceiling roses, reverse cycle airconditioner, Settler wood burner and more to appreciate when viewed. The rural surrounds and gardens consist of mature fruit trees, olive trees, fenced dam, garden sheds, water tank and huge shed (4 plus vehicles) and roofline storage. Separate guest accommodation (consists of 2 bedrooms, attic, living and bathroom/laundry) suits extended family, teenage retreat, professional home office or consulting rooms or maybe B&B (STCA). No. 66 has a wide front verandah with north-western orientation which makes the home light and bright throughout. The location provides for a genuine country and coastal living atmosphere with all the convenience and services of Drysdale only minutes away. The owners have purchased for permanent living, however interstate employment is necessary and they are ready to go ... Perfect living ready for the new owner. Ring to make an appointment.

Description:
Stunning Coastal Appeal
Here is your opportunity to secure a brand new, high quality, spacious home with nothing more to do but move in. This home offers first home buyers and young families an opportunity to start out with an eye for style. Designed and constructed with clever planning and careful thought, it maximises the advantages of the 575 sqm block. Located in the prestigious Curlewis Park Estate within walking distance of the beach, schools, parks, tennis courts and shops.
Comprising of three spacious bedrooms, the master bedroom featuring ensuite and WIR, open contemporary design, modern kitchen just begging to entertain (with 4 meter Essastone bench top, Euro appliances and Butlers pantry), separate living zone, family bathroom and separate laundry.
Add to the layout the spotted gum hardwood flooring, reverse cycle air-conditioning, ducted gas heating, optic fibre cabling, high ceilings throughout, LED push button switches and you will enjoy the space and lifestyle this home can offer.
Outside is a further Alfresco entertaining area, grass area for the kids to play, double garage, landscaped gardens and side drive access for boat or caravan.
* Brand new light filled home

* Open plan design

* Close to beach, shops and schools

Description:
Family Fantastic!
In a suburb that is renowned for being family friendly (offering a wide range of opportunities for adults and children alike), it is not just the township that speaks to the needs and desires of the Smith's, Jones's and perhaps not-so-average clan...this home answers a number of questions about not only the basics, but also the lifestyle that goes hand in hand with a coastal residency.
Just a few years young, you have the benefit here of being able to purchase a near new home with all of the modern comforts you would aspire to, with the added bonus of the outdoor infrastructure being completed and ready to enjoy. Situated on a gently sloping 723 sqm allotment, the entertaining and dedicated play areas are separated by an inviting expanse of lawn and central garden beds, ultimately ensuring that family members and guests of all ages have the space to relax and unwind.
The home itself is arranged over three levels to gain the best possible use of the both floor area and the surrounding land. Entry to the home is achieved by either the contemporary front door, or the secure internal access from the double garage, both of which lead into the passage that provides a space saving European laundry and handy powder room that also services the study / fourth bedroom on this level. The master bedroom is also located on this level away from the bustle of the upper level living and lower level children's retreat. Boasting a modern ensuite and WIR, your privacy is most definitely assured.
Stunning polished timber floors grace the living space and provide the perfect complement to the open, yet cleverly zoned lounge and dining areas separated by a top quality and beautifully appointed kitchen with designer lighting and glass splash-backs above the 900mm stainless steel cooker. A dishwasher and sink in the l-shaped island allow for an abundance of work surface and breakfast bar whilst the walk in pantry is perfect for storage of food and smaller appliances. Overlooking the charming rural landscape and decked alfresco, this is sure to be the true heart of the home.
Downstairs, children have two large bedrooms to sleep in with their own bathroom, separate WC and rumpus room with direct access to a further entertaining area and the garden. Talk about spoilt! Teenagers, in particular, will relish the freedom and seclusion they can achieve in this area.
Finished in the all-important neutral tones with sought after features such as square stopped ceilings, split system air conditioning, ducted heating and downlights, this is a delightful example of current trends that will not date for many, many years to come. A combination of well positioned highlight and conventional windows flood the home with natural light, minimising energy bills and making the home a pleasant refuge from the daily work routine.
Within a short drive of all amenities in the busy Drysdale town centre, excellent options for schooling and all of the fun of the nearby beaches and sporting facilities, this home is also a short 15 minutes from Geelong and therefore the ideal haven for YOUR family.
- Close to all amenities.
- Coastal location 15 minutes from Geelong
- Near new 3/4 bedroom home
- Beautifully presented/nothing to do
- Spacious home and gardens
Terms: 10% deposit, balance 60/90/120 days
Land: 723 sq m approx.

Description:
Classic cedar home
Highly appealing cedar weatherboard home close to township. Grand timber stair entry to the verandah. Cathedral timber ceilings are a highlight in the open plan living, dining and kitchen. Beautifully polished Tasmanian Oak timber floors. Kitchen is a treat to cook in with stainless steel appliances including a 900mm standalone oven with gas hotplates, dishwasher, corner pantry & plenty of bench space. Traditional cedar windows offering plenty of light in all living areas and bedrooms. Timber French doors open out to a classic verandah entertaining area. Master bedroom with timber French doors opening out to the verandah, walk through robe & ensuite. Central bathroom with corner spa bath. Large laundry with plenty of cupboard storage. 2nd & 3rd bedrooms with built in robes, 4th bedroom would make an exceptional study. Delightful gardens with a paved outdoor entertaining area to enjoy the sunny days. Double carport with a large enough area to store boats or caravans. Central heating & cooling. This home contains all the classic features you would expect from a house of this quality. Located close to the centre of town; offering easy access to schools, shopping, the McLeod Waterholes & Lake Lorne.
